{"lemma":"سَبِيكَةٍ","slug":"سَبِيكَةٍ","root":"س.ب.ك","root_slug":"س-ب-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ب-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18804"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a piece of molten metal, bullion, ingot, alloy etc."}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sa.biː.ka/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18804","headword_ar":"سَبِيكَةٌ","root":"sbk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[a subst. formed from the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabiykN","text_ar":"سَبِيكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"by the affix"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An ingot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Mgh, Msb, K) of gold, (Lth, Mgh, Msb, TA,) or of silver, (Lth, S, Mgh, TA,) &c., (Mgh,) [i. e.,] sometimes, of any metal, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of an oblong form,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has been melted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, Mgh, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and cleared of its dross,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and poured forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into a mould,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) [i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misobakap","text_ar":"مِسْبَكَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of iron like the half of a cane divided lengthwise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaAy^iku","text_ar":"سَبَايِكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth, S, Msb.) An Arab of the desert likened to it a difficult mountain that he desired to ascend, because of its smoothness; saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~u sabiykapK h`*ihi","text_ar":"اَىُّ سَبِيكَةٍ هٰذِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What an ingot is this !"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b2-  The pl. is also applied to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuqaAq","text_ar":"وُقَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thin, flat, bread"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; this being so called because it is made of choice, or pure, flour; and is as though it were prepared therefrom by being melted and poured into a mould ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA^an~ahu subika minoha","text_ar":"كَاَنَّهُ سُبِكَ مِنْهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and cleared from the bran. (TA.)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1301}],"source_refs":["Lth","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}